10 A Joint Resolution directing the Secretary of State
to refer to the people for their approval or
11 rejection a proposed amendment to the Oklahoma
Constitution by adding a new Section 6 to Article
12 III; requiring proof of identity to vote in certain
elections; requiring proof of identity for all
13 authorized methods of voting; requiring Legislature
to enact specific requirements for proof of identity;
14 providing ballot title; ordering special election on
certain date; and directing filing.
15
16
17 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
18 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
19 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
20 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
21 the following proposed amendment to the Oklahoma Constitution by
22 adding a new Section 6 to Article III to read as follows:
23 Section 6. Each voter shall present proof of identity to the
24 appropriate election official when voting at any election authorized
SJR47 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 by l aw and conducted by a county election board or the State
2 Election Board. Proof of identity shall be required for any method
3 of voting authorized by law. The Legislature shall enact laws
4 necessary to specify the requirements for proof of identity for
5 voting as required by this section.
6 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
7 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
8 the following form:
9 BALLOT TITLE
10 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
11 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
12 This measure adds Section 6 to Article 3 of the Oklahoma
13 Constitution to require proof of identity to vote in any
14 election authorized by law and conducted by a county election
15 board or the State Election Board. The measure requires proof
16 of identity for all authorized methods of voting. The measure
17 requires the Legislature to enact laws to specify requirements
18 for proof of identity for voting.
19 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
20 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
21 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
22 SECTION 3. A special election is hereby ordered to be held
23 throughout the State of Oklahoma on the date of August 25, 2026, at
24 which time the proposed amendment to the Oklahoma Constitution, as
SJR47 HFLR Page 2
